@startuml class_diagram

title Calculator — Class Diagram

package "src" {

    class Calculator {
        + add(a: float, b: float) : float
        + subtract(a: float, b: float) : float
        + multiply(a: float, b: float) : float
        + divide(a: float, b: float) : float
        + power(base: float, exponent: float) : float
        + square(a: float) : float
        + cube(a: float) : float
        + square_root(a: float) : float
        + cube_root(a: float) : float
        + log(a: float) : float
        + ln(a: float) : float
        + factorial(n: int) : int
    }

    class TooManyAttemptsError {
    }

    class "__main__" as Main {
        - OPERATIONS : dict
        - MAX_ATTEMPTS : int
        - HISTORY_FILE : str
        + _fmt_num(x) : str
        + _format_entry(method_name: str, operands: tuple, result) : str
        + _write_history(history: list[str], path: str) : None
        + _read_number(prompt: str, max_attempts: int) : float
        + run_session(calc: Calculator, history_file: str) : None
        + main() : None
    }

    Main --> Calculator : uses
    Main ..> TooManyAttemptsError : raises / catches
}

class "main" as CLI {
    - CLI_OPERATIONS : dict
    + _parse_operand(raw: str) : float
    + run_cli(args: list[str]) : None
}

CLI --> Calculator : uses
CLI --> Main : delegates interactive_main()

note right of Calculator
  Validation rules:
  divide: b != 0
  square_root: a >= 0
  cube_root: handles negative (sign-preserving)
  log: a > 0
  ln: a > 0
  factorial: n >= 0, integer, not bool
end note

note right of Main
  OPERATIONS dict maps menu keys (1..12)
  to method names, operand count, and labels.
  run_session() loops until user enters "0".
  MAX_ATTEMPTS = 5: session terminates after
  5 consecutive invalid menu choices or 5
  consecutive invalid number inputs.
  _read_number() raises TooManyAttemptsError
  when the attempt limit is reached.
  History: each successful calculation is
  appended to a list in function-call style
  (e.g. add(2, 3) = 5). On session exit,
  _write_history() saves the list to
  HISTORY_FILE ("history.txt"). The user
  can view history mid-session via "h".
end note

note right of CLI
  CLI_OPERATIONS dict maps operation name strings
  to (operand_count, method_name) pairs.
  run_cli() dispatches one operation per invocation.
  Errors printed to stderr; exits with code 1.
  Falls back to interactive_main() when no args given.
end note

@enduml
